-------------- Chapter 2 ----------------------------------------------------

             @{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}
             ------------

    What can Learn-chess be used for?


CHESS-EDUCATION + PLAYING CHESS + CHESS-TOOL + CHESS-DATABASE 

* Learn chess (to move the pieces)

* Learn positional play (activity, centre)

* Play without loosing pieces by accident

* Training chess or problems

* Look at commented games

* Play chess computer against computer, person against computer, person
  against person (from v2.7 a lot stronger chess engine)

* Error free typing of games with comments into text files or prints

* Printout games with comments in short or long form to printer or file

* Make database of your own or other's games with comments

* Checking games in text files for errors

* Read games and rewrite to get a homogenous text-format

* Make Chess-problems

* Analysing

* Showing commented games and problems for other people (on standard TV)

* Read and write games in the standard @{"PGN" Link "PGN"} text files

* Get database of games through e.g. NICBASE, WRITE TO TEXT FILE @{"Import" Link "Import"}

* Get database of games through future releases of games-disks
  (1-96: 100.000 games)

* Use your own language and piece-letters (LOCALE-file)

* Print high-quality diagrams using the included type 1 chess-piece font.

