3.3

   @{b}Writing of game to textfiles or printer:@{ub}

<Disk/Printer icon: Printer>

If writing is made to a textfile (other name than prt:), there will be placed
a ; (semicolon) before all comments (if LONGFORMWRITE=ON) or () (punctuation 
marks) around. That makes sure that the written game can be read again with
the comments intact. 

If the game has an alternative startposition, it will be written
(as a text-only position).

    NOTE: If written in the @{"PGN" Link "PGN"} format, an alternative
          start-position will be written as a @{"FEN" Link "FEN"} tag.

If you write to an existing textfile (OK when asked), the game will be append-
ed, while PIG (SK20) and Saved (SK10,SK11) format files will be overwritten.

If you make a comment to a position containing the text-string:
<dia>  there will be written a diagram in the textformat used with the
Chess-font. (see font/Font.Doc) @{" Try to see it " Link "ChessFontType1/Font.Doc/Main"}

PGN text format is used if @{"tool type" Link "ToolTypes"} LONGFORMWRITE=OFF.
If @{"tool type" Link "ToolTypes"} PGN=ON will PGN-@{"NAG" Link "NAG"}s be used (see @{"PGN" Link "PGN"} standard).

A long notation-form is used (one fullmove/line) if LONGFORMWRITE=ON

English piece letters are used when INTERNATIONAL=ON
National piece letters are used when INTERNATIONAL=OFF

