3.5

  @{b}How to play against the computer@{ub}

1. Click the Board icon if you want to turn the board around

2. Click on the Man icon above the board icon if present to set the Computer
   to play that side. 

   NOTE: the man/computer eyes indicates whom to make next move, the mouth
         indicates the overall evaluation of the position.
         
3. If none of the three thinking-strength icon to the right of the Computer
   icon is active then activate the wanted one to start computer thinking.

4. To move see @{"Board:" Link "Walk"}

   NOTE: the mouth on a piece indicates the activity for that piece. 

   NOTE: the time used for each move is directly related to the complexity
         of the position. Many pieces attacked, checks possible and promotable
         pawns can extent the search from 1-3 upto 20-24 half-moves.

   NOTE: the 'chess-clock' was not intended as a user feature, but is a test
         feature I found too nice to disable. See history for description.
