8.1

  @{b}Features:@{ub}

       *  @{"Import" Link "Import"}/export in the standard @{"PGN" Link "PGN"} text format for chess-games.

       *  External NICto@{"PGN" Link "PGN"} conversion tool to @{"import" Link "Import"} games from the
          NICbase3 chess database on the PC.

       *  External PIG copying/appending tool (ConcatPIG)

       *  Chess-Font to support High Quality diagrams printed via a text
          processor. Adobe Type 1 format. @{" Try to see Font.Doc " Link "ChessFontType1/Font.Doc/Main"}

       *  Highly compressed PIG file format. One 880K disc can contain
          around 6500 games (compressed 4.6 times compared to the @{"PGN" Link "PGN"} format).

       *  Advanced searching on positions, variations and information tags.

       *  Upto 16*64K games can be selected by a search

       *  Several thousand games on the data disc, and more than 80.000 
          games are accessible in the PIG format.

       *  Works on AGA and WB 3.1

       *  Can still run on a standard A500 / 1Mb / WB1.3 / no harddisc.

       *  Uses from 500kb and up to 2-12 Mb ram if useful, available and
          allowed by setup.

       *  LOCALE language support in an open format. 

       *  Integrated with Learn-Chess (educational chess-program)

       *  Prepared pseudo-hierachical opening analyser
          (from v2.5: implemented as a game-tree generator)

       *  Different piece-set is loaded if "ilbm" directory found with the
          pieces in IFF-ILBM files named: 001 (white square), 002 (black
          square), 010-027 (white squared mMkKqQtTrRbBnNeEpP, see @{"3.2" Link "ReadAsciiOrPgn"}),
          110-127 (black squared), even=white pieces, odd=BLACK PIECES. All
          must have the same size as 001. Set the @{"Tooltype" Link "Settings"} MOUTHOFF=ON
          to avoid mouths.

      *   Scans more than 500 games/second on a A1200 with HD and fast-ram.

      *   Make ECO and NIC keys.
 
      *   Make Tournament Tables out of games.

      *   Advanced search using position-patterns @{"Search Patterns" Link "SearchPatterns"}

       THE PIG format can have up to 29 @{"PGN" Link "PGN"} information tags and can have
       comments to every position. A game is allowed to fill up to 32K and
       have up to 1023 halfmoves. A PIG file can be compressed further
       35-40 % with lha (giving about 10000 games on one disc).

